Serbia May Hold General Elections in Early April, Novosti Says

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-06-29T06:30:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/serbia-may-hold-general-elections-in-early-april-novosti-says.html
Serbia’s ruling coalition may choose
the first half of April to hold general elections,  Vecernje
Novosti  newspaper reported, citing unidentified people.  The government, led by President Boris Tadic’s Democrats,
will continue to defy opposition demands to hold the ballot
sooner, the newspaper reported, adding that elections for the
national parliament and local assemblies will be held at the
same time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  